rowing.'),(115,'video-2-subtitles','Before it stops: another four billion people will be added to the world population.'),(116,'video-2-subtitles','Four billion more. That\'s a lot of people!'),(117,'video-2-subtitles','But the longer poor children keeps dying and this change is delayed:'),(118,'video-2-subtitles','the more billions will be added.'),(119,'video-2-subtitles','So ending population growth starts by saving the poorest children.'),(120,'a-WaffleCategoryThing-name','Afghanistan'),(121,'a-WaffleCategoryThing-name','Angola'),(122,'a-WaffleCategoryThing-name','United Arab Emirates'),(123,'a-VideoFile-title','New Video'),(124,'a-VideoFile-caption','At vero eos et accusam'),(125,'a-VideoFile-about','Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetuer adipiscing elit, sed diam nonummy nibh euismod tincidunt ut laoreet dolore magna aliquam erat volutpat.'),(126,'video-8-subtitles','A common misunderstanding is that if we save all the poor children: the world will become overpopulated...'),(127,'video-8-subtitles','This may sound logical, but it\'s wrong.'),(128,'video-8-subtitles','Its the other way around!'),(129,'video-8-subtitles','Saving the poor childrens lives is required to end population growth.'),(130,'video-8-subtitles','Now! Look at the UN numbers.'),(131,'video-8-subtitles','Poor parents on avarage have five children. And one dies.'),(132,'video-8-subtitles','Look! Two parents are replaced by four surviving children in the next generation.'),(133,'video-8-subtitles','This means the population is growing very fast among the poorest.'),(134,'video-8-subtitles','This is the avarage family in the worst of places like Congo and Afghanistan.'),(135,'video-8-subtitles','Today, where child mortality is highest, that\'s where the population is growing faster than anywhere else.'),(136,'video-8-subtitles','How many people live like this?'),(137,'video-8-subtitles','There are seven billion people in the world. One block: one billion.'),(138,'video-8-subtitles','The poorest two billion...'),(139,'video-8-subtitles','...they live like this.'),(140,'video-8-subtitles','The other five billion...'),(141,'video-8-subtitles','...they have this avarage family. Two parents having two children and there are few child deaths.'),(142,'video-8-subtitles','This is the majority of the world population, not only Europe and the US.'),(143,'video-8-subtitles','It\'s throughout religions and cultures: China, Iran, Mexico, large cities in Africa.'),(144,'video-8-subtitles','Today in most populations children just replace parents.'),(145,'video-8-subtitles','And the size of generations are no longer increasing.'),(146,'video-8-subtitles','This means: the population will stop growing.'),(147,'video-8-subtitles','How did so many people end up with small families?'),(148,'video-8-subtitles','Well,  their children stopped dying.'),(149,'video-8-subtitles','As they left extreme poverty and girls got education: parents no longer had to'),(150,'video-8-subtitles','compensate for child death by having many babies. And a large family stopped being'),(151,'video-8-subtitles','an economic necessity or a social status symbol.'),(152,'video-8-subtitles','And with modern contraceptives: parents across the world, the majority'),(153,'video-8-subtitles','decided to have a small family.'),(154,'video-8-subtitles','So by saving the lives of poor children and helping the last two billion out of poverty:'),(155,'video-8-subtitles','These parents will also decide to have fewer children.'),(156,'video-8-subtitles','And fewer.'),(157,'video-8-subtitles','Eventually...'),(158,'video-8-subtitles','...reaching the two child family'),(159,'video-8-subtitles','That showed the UN family size forcast up to the end of the century.'),(160,'video-8-subtitles','Then the world population is expected to stop growing.'),(161,'video-8-subtitles','Before it stops: another four billion people will be added to the world population.'),(162,'video-8-subtitles','Four billion more. That\'s a lot o